      "span_text": "Regression analyses show no relationship between the percent gains in either fitness or ambulatory function, and the baseline severity of hemiparetic gait deficits, initial fitness levels (VO 2 peak), age, or time between the stroke and starting exercise (range 6 months to 10 years).  This promising finding suggests that large numbers of stroke patients may benefit from structured exercise therapy to improve ambulatory function and fitness even years after a stroke."
